The Latest from Week 18 of the NFL (all times Eastern):___12:05 p.m.The NFL’s first 17-game regular season is set to wrap up, and the final game will be a playoffs-or-bust meeting between the Los Angeles Chargers and Las Vegas Raiders.The AFC West rivals are chasing one of the AFC’s two remaining postseason spots in the night game.Ben Roethlisberger still has playoff hopes in his final season, a week after the star quarterback’s farewell in Pittsburgh. The Steelers have to beat Baltimore and hope Indianapolis loses at two-win Jacksonville. With those two outcomes in the early games, the only thing that could keep Pittsburgh out is a Chargers-Raiders tie.The Colts are in with a win or tie against the Jaguars. The Ravens need a victory and quite a bit of help.San Francisco has the inside track to the last of the seven playoff spots in the NFC. It will be decided during the late games.ADVERTISEMENTThe 49ers are in with a victory over the Los Angeles Rams, who have already qualified and can clinch the NFC West with a win. New Orleans gets in with a victory over Atlanta and a San Francisco loss.___More AP NFL: https://apnews.com/hub/nfl and https://apnews.com/hub/pro-32 and https://twitter.com/AP_NFL